# Local Agent Preferences (Example)

This file is inspired by Claude-style local memory, but Codex does not automatically
load `AGENTS.local.md` when a repository already has a root `AGENTS.md`.

Use this example in one of three ways:
- copy useful lines into your user-level `~/.codex/config.toml` as
  `developer_instructions`
- keep a private local note and reference it in your prompt when needed
- adapt the ideas into a nested `AGENTS.override.md` for a specific subtree if the rules
  should apply to everyone working there

## Example personal preferences
- Prefer concise commentary updates.
- Use my preferred test fixture names and sample accounts.
- Avoid touching generated lockfiles unless the task requires it.
- Ask before adding new dependencies.
- When blocked, leave the unblock in `work/ACTIVE_TASKS.md`.
